513. messae ad lunam. Charms gathered by moonlight were supposed to be specially powerful. Cf. the ingredients of the witches' caldron in Macbeth.

514. cum lacte qualifies herbae like an adjective.

515. Foals when newly born were supposed to have a lump on their forehead which the mother bit off. If it was taken before she could do so, she went mad. The lump was considered a powerful love-charm (amor).
